BaseLocalTimeConverter, BaseStringConverter, BaseTimeConverter, BooleanConverter, BytesConverter, ClassConverter, ConfidenceConverter, CountConverter, DoubleConverter, DurationConverter, DurationInMillisecondsConverter, DurationInSecondsConverter, EnumConverter, EpochTimeConverter, EstimateConverter, FloatConverter, FormattedDoubleConverter, FormattedIntegerConverter, FormattedLongConverter, FrequencyConverter, HexadecimalLongConverter, HttpDateTimeConverter, HumanizedKivaKitLocalDateTimeConverter, IdentifierConverter, IdentityConverter, IntegerConverter, IntegerIdentifierConverter, IsoDateTimeConverter, IsoLocalDateTimeConverter, KivaKitLocalDateConverter, KivaKitLocalDateTimeConverter, KivaKitLocalDateTimeWithMillisecondsConverter, KivaKitLocalDateTimeWithSecondsConverter, KivaKitLocalTimeConverter, KivaKitUtcTimeConverter, LevelConverter, LocaleLanguageConverter, LongConverter, LongValuedConverter, MaximumConverter, MinimumConverter, ObjectListConverter, ObjectSetConverter, PatternConverter, PercentConverter, ThrowableConverter, VersionConverter, ZoneIdConverter
public interface StringConverter<Value> extends TwoWayConverter<String,Value>, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.Parsable<Value>
A bidirectional converter between String values and values of the given type. The Converter interface converts from String to type <Value> and the method TwoWayConverter.unconvert(Object) converts a <Value> back to a String.

Parsing

  • parse(String) - Implements Parsable by calling Converter.convert(Object)

Collections

  • convertToList(String, String) - Converts the given text and separator to an ObjectList using this converter
  • convertToList(Iterable) - Converts the given sequence of objects to an ObjectList using this converter
  • convertToSet(String, String) - Converts the given text and separator to an ObjectSet using this converter
  • convertToSet(Iterable) - Converts the given sequence of objects to an ObjectSet using this converter
  • listConverter(Class) - Returns a StringConverter<ObjectList> that converts text to an object list using this converter
  • listConverter(Class, String) - Returns a StringConverter<ObjectList> that converts text and a separator to an object list using this converter
  • setConverter(Class) - Returns a StringConverter<ObjectSet> that converts text to an object set using this converter
  • setConverter(Class, String) - Returns a StringConverter<ObjectSet> that converts text and a separator to an object set using this converter

Reverse Conversion

  • unconvertAll(Iterable) - Returns a sequence of values to a StringList

jonathanl (shibo)
